children.label: search
description:
Searches using the given `search` method. Overrides the `AbortSignal` with one that will abort
either when the request times out, or when the original `AbortSignal` is aborted. Updates
`pendingCount$` when the request is started/finalized.
returnComment: `Observable` emitting the search response or an error.

classes.label: SearchTimeoutError
description: Request Failure - When an entire multi request fails

functions.label: waitUntilNextSessionCompletes$
description:
Creates an observable that emits when next search session completes.
This utility is helpful to use in the application to delay some tasks until next session completes.

functions.label: searchUsageObserver
description: Rxjs observer for easily doing `tap(searchUsageObserver(logger, usage))` in an rxjs chain.

children.label: registerSearchStrategy
description:
Extension point exposed for other plugins to register their own search
strategies.

children.label: usage
description: Used internally for telemetry

children.label: getSearchStrategy
description:
Get other registered search strategies by name (or, by default, the Elasticsearch strategy).
For example, if a new strategy needs to use the already-registered ES search strategy, it can
use this function to accomplish that.

interfaces.label: ISearchStrategy
description:
Search strategy interface contains a search method that takes in a request and returns a promise
that resolves to a response.

children.label: ensureIds
description:
Ensure that all of the objects in the list have ids, the objects
and list are modified by reference.

children.label: list
description: - a list of objects, objects can be anything really

returnComment: - the list that was passed in

children.label: nextId
description: Calculate the next id based on the ids in this list
returnComment: list - a list of objects with id properties

children.label: setParams
description: Write the current values to this.params, filling in the defaults as we go

children.label: from
description:
- optional object to read values from,
 used when initializing

children.label: onSearchRequestStart
description: Hook for pre-flight logic, see AggType#onSearchRequestStart

children.label: toDsl
description:
Convert this aggConfig to its dsl syntax.

Adds params and adhoc subaggs to a pojo, then returns it

children.label: aggConfigs
description: - the config object to convert

returnComment:
- if the config has a dsl representation, it is
  returned, else undefined is returned

returnComment: Returns a serialized representation of an AggConfig.

children.label: toSerializedFieldFormat
description:
Returns a serialized field format for the field used in this agg.
This can be passed to fieldFormats.deserialize to get the field
format instance.

children.label: toExpressionAst
returnComment: Returns an ExpressionAst representing the this agg type.

children.label: getValueBucketPath
description:
Returns the bucket path containing the main value the agg will produce
(e.g. for sum of bytes it will point to the sum, for median it will point
 to the 50 percentile in the percentile multi value bucket)

Checks whether a given Elasticsearch interval is a calendar or fixed interval
and returns an object containing the appropriate date_histogram property for that
interval. So it will return either an object containing the fixed_interval key for
that interval or a calendar_interval. If the specified interval was not a valid Elasticsearch

You can simply spread the returned value of this method into your date_histogram.

functions.label: isValidEsInterval
description:
Checks whether a given interval string (e.g. 1w, 24h, ...) is a valid Elasticsearch interval.
Will return false if the interval is not valid in Elasticsearch, otherwise true.
Invalid intervals might be: 2f, since there is no unit 'f'; 2w, since weeks and month intervals
are only allowed with a value of 1, etc.

children.label: interval
description: The interval string like 1w, 24h

returnComment: True if the interval is valid for Elasticsearch

functions.label: parseEsInterval
description:
Extracts interval properties from an ES interval string. Disallows unrecognized interval formats
and fractional values. Converts some intervals from "calendar" to "fixed" when the number of
units is larger than 1, and throws an error for others.

Conversion rules:

| Interval | Single unit type | Multiple units type |
| -------- | ---------------- | ------------------- |
| ms       | fixed            | fixed               |
| s        | fixed            | fixed               |
| m        | calendar         | fixed               |
| h        | calendar         | fixed               |
| d        | calendar         | fixed               |
| w        | calendar         | N/A - disallowed    |
| M        | calendar         | N/A - disallowed    |
| y        | calendar         | N/A - disallowed    |
